  "prompt": "What are the recipes of five minutes easy to make snacks?",
  "response": "Certainly! Here are five easy-to-make snack recipes that you can whip up in about five minutes each:\n\n### 1. **Apple Slice with Peanut Butter**\n**Ingredients:**\n- 1 apple (any variety)\n- 2 tablespoons peanut butter\n\n**Instructions:**\n1. Core and slice the apple into rounds or wedges.\n2. Spread a layer of peanut butter on each slice.\n3. Enjoy immediately or pack in a snack container for later.\n\n### 2. **Yogurt and Berry Parfait**\n**Ingredients:**\n- 1 cup Greek yogurt\n- A handful of fresh berries (strawberries, blueberries, raspberries)\n- 1 tablespoon honey or maple syrup (optional)\n- 1 tablespoon granola (optional)\n\n**Instructions:**\n1. Scoop yogurt into a bowl or glass.\n2. Layer with berries on top.\n3. Drizzle with honey or maple syrup if desired.\n4. Sprinkle with granola for extra crunch.\n\n### 3. **Cheese and Crackers**\n**Ingredients:**\n- Assorted crackers\n- Various cheeses (cheddar, brie, gouda, etc.)\n- Optional: sliced cucumber, cherry tomatoes, olives\n\n**Instructions:**\n1. Arrange crackers on a plate.\n2. Slice cheese and place on top of or next to the crackers.\n3. Add any optional extras like cucumber slices, cherry tomatoes, or olives for added flavor and nutrition.\n\n### 4. **Nut Butter Banana Roll-Up**\n**Ingredients:**\n- 1 whole-wheat tortilla\n- 1 tablespoon almond butter or peanut butter\n- 1 banana\n\n**Instructions:**\n1. Spread nut butter evenly over the tortilla.\n2. Place the peeled banana at one end of the tortilla.\n3. Roll the tortilla around the banana.\n4. Slice into rounds and serve.\n\n### 5. **Avocado Toast**\n**Ingredients:**\n- 1 slice whole-grain bread\n- 1/2 ripe avocado\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- Optional: red pepper flakes, cherry tomatoes, or a poached egg\n\n**Instructions:**\n1. Toast the bread to your desired level of crispiness.\n2. Mash the avocado and spread it on the toast.\n3. Add a pinch of salt and pepper.\n4. Top with optional extras like a sprinkle of red pepper flakes, sliced cherry tomatoes, or a poached egg.\n\nFeel free to customize these snacks based on your preferences and what you have on hand. Enjoy!",
